  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Treatment with Nintendo wii is higher to physical therapy conventional in the quality of life
      and motor performance in patients with Parkinson's disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to assess if the treatment of rehabilitation with Nintendo wii is
      higher to the conventional in the quality of life and motor performance in patients with
      Parkinson's disease.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
